    <note>Kong(2) Yanzhi [902] Luguo Kongzi's descendants lived in Yanzhou, Qufou xian for 48 generations before his fifth generation ancestor, Ji [3437], was appointed to a post in Jizhou during the Tang where he died in office. His family did not return north and this branch of the lineage became Linjiang jun, Xingan residents. Pingzhong's [901], Wuzhong's [3438] and Wenzhong's [3439] father. XCB, 213.12a, 215.9b; Jiangxi TZ, 21.14b; Guangxi TZ, 21.15a-15b; Su Song, WJ, 59.1a; Songshi yi, 1.10b; Zeng Gong, WJ, 42.10b-12b. CBD, 1, 391.</note>
